    "Body": " Senior Manager, Data Governance and Tools Ingevity - 3.9 North Charleston, SC Apply Now Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $140,000 - $190,000 a year Benefits Relocation Assistance Qualifications Data Management Customer Service Manufacturing Visio Analysis Skills Bachelor's Degree Full Job Description Job Family Group: Information Technology Overview Bold. Energetic. Ingenious. Genuine. These qualities best describe employees who work for Ingevity. We believe it takes extraordinary people to create extraordinary results. At Ingevity, we harness the bold spirit, innate curiosity and remarkable ingenuity of our people to develop innovations that purify, protect and enhance the world around us. Our products enable oil to flow better, crops to grow fuller, roads last longer, and ensure that the air we all breathe is cleaner. Already a leader in markets in which we compete, we leverage our deep technical expertise and knowledge of our customers\u2019 industries to turn complex challenges into powerful possibilities and value-added solutions. We prize creativity and imagination and we\u2019re always looking for a better, smarter way of doing things. We know it takes the right people with the right attitude to achieve the improbable. People who understand that there is no challenge too big and no contribution too small. People with the ability to solve and the commitment to stay the course. People who work together to create meaningful impact and exponential results, for our customers and the world around us. Our people are our most valued asset, and the foundation of our success. Interested? We thought you might be, and we\u2019re so glad! How you\u2019ll impact Ingevity: Support the roll out of an enterprise wide data governance framework, with a focus on the improvement of data quality and the protection of sensitive data through modifications to organization behavior, policies and standards, principles, governance metrics, processes, and implementation of related tools and data architecture. Design, implement and manage Master Data Management tools and processes. Define roles and responsibilities related to data governance and tools. Responsible for ensuring consistent, accurate, complete, accessible and timely data. Maintain strategic alignment and compliance with US and international data privacy regulations (eg. GDPR, CCPA) by collaborating with Legal, Internal/External Audit and IT leaders. Serve as a liaison between Business and Functional areas and IT to ensure that data related business requirements for the protection of sensitive data are implemented leveraging data governance tools and best practices. Act as an agent of change to help drive data best practices and evangelize the concept of \u201cdata as an asset\u201d. Define indicators of performance and quality metrics and ensure compliance with data related policies, processes, standards, roles and responsibilities, and adoption requirements. Manage a team of Data Analysts. What you need to succeed: Bachelor\u2019s degree required. Management Information Systems, Engineering, Business or related disciplines preferred. Minimum of five years of management or team leadership experience in IT or data governance with increasing responsibility, within a manufacturing environment, required. Experience in an enterprise IT and / or cross-functional Data Management role required. Experience working within a data governance team (eg. data governance council or data management COE) required. Working knowledge and experience of data governance & data management as operating models (organization and business process perspective) required. Demonstrated experience in information technology and data governance related change management, required. Hands-on experience with data governance and data management software and prior implementation experience required, SAP MDG preferred. Technical knowledge of core data management components such as data warehouses, SAP MD service models, integration, data analytics and reporting, required. Experience with SAP products and solutions required, preferably in a SAP for Chemicals/Manufacturing environment. Strong oral and written communication skills; ability to communicate and influence at all levels of the organization to deliver innovative and cost-effective solutions. Proven change management and relationship building experience. Excellent problem solving, dispute resolution, interpersonal, analytical and project management skills; ability to prioritize, delegate tasks and multi-task. Strong focus on collaboration, team building, and customer service. Deep working knowledge and experience with professional organizations such as the Data Governance Institute (DGI), Data Governance Professionals Organization (DGPO), or similar. Data governance certifications highly desirable. Ability to look across the business to determine linkages, process improvements, and possible roadblocks. Capability to interpret strategy and roadmaps into implementation and create value for the business. Demonstrated skill running effective meetings and gaining buy-in and participation from colleagues at all levels within the organization. Strong Microsoft Office skills - Word, Excel, Visio, PowerPoint, MS Project, MS SharePoint. Must be willing to travel globally up to 25%. Travel should be minimal, but projects could necessitate short-term, intense travel. This position is eligible for relocation assistance. This role is not eligible for employment visa sponsorship. The successful candidate must not now, or in the future, require sponsorship to work in the US. Ingevity is an Equal Opportunity Employer, Minorities/Women/Veterans/Disabled. Recruiting Agencies: Ingevity does not accept unsolicited resumes and therefore, will not be responsible for any fees associated with unsolicited resumes. "
